  "prompt": "What is the origin of Snow White?",
  "response": "The story of Snow White originates from a fairy tale first published by the Brothers Grimm in their collection \"Grimms' Fairy Tales\" in 1812. The original German version is called \"Schneewittchen\" (Snow White). However, the tale likely has even older roots in European folklore.\n\nThe Grimm Brothers' version differs significantly from modern adaptations, such as Disney's animated film. In the original story, the evil queen (Snow White's stepmother) is more grotesque, and the ending involves her being forced to dance in red-hot iron shoes until she dies.\n\nThe basic plot involves a beautiful young princess whose stepmother is jealous of her beauty and tries to kill her. Snow White escapes and finds refuge with seven dwarfs, and eventually is saved by a prince who revives her with a kiss.\n\nWhile the Grimm Brothers' version is the most well-known, similar stories exist in various European folklore traditions. Some scholars believe the tale might have been inspired by real historical figures or composite stories from different cultural narratives.\n\nThe story has been adapted numerous times in literature, film, and other media, with Disney's 1937 animated film being perhaps the most famous modern interpretation.",
